title: 97A.531 SHIPPING WILD ANIMALS TAKEN IN CANADA.
text:
A person may ship, within or out of the state, wild animals lawfully taken and possessed in Canada and that have lawfully entered the state. The shipment must have the shipping coupons required for a shipment originating in the province where the animals were taken.
